ton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532308\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532308\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tef1665702691693.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tef1665702691693.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tef1665702691693.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tef1665702691693\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"tef1665702691693__uedelete_401737\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Close down the Uniface environment that was created by <code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"tef1665702691693__topic_d119090e1_d119091e1_d119092e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tef1665702691693__p_d119093e1_d119094e1_d119095e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">long uedelete (UHACT</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">hEnv</var>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">int</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">how</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">);</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tef1665702691693__topic_d84892e1_d84893e1_d84894e1_d84895e1_d84896e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d866720e76\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"tef1665702691693__parml_vvg_1ds_zvb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">hEnv</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The Uniface environment handle that was returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code>.\n               </dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">how</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">A value specifying how you want to shut down the environment. Valid values are:\n                     <ul class=\"ul\" id=\"tef1665702691693__ul_vbt_cds_zvb\">\n<li class=\"li\">1—Suspend Uniface session, clear screen, and return control of keyboard and\n                        screen to the 3GL application.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">0—Suspend Uniface session and return control of keyboard to the 3GL\n                        application.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">-1—Terminate the Uniface session completely.</li>\n</ul>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tef1665702691693__topic_d84897e1_d84898e1_d84899e1_d84900e1_d84901e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d866720e120\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by uedelete</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1__entry__2\">Error constant</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1__entry__3\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1__entry__1\">1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">UINI_SUCCESS</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1__entry__3\">Success</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1__entry__1\">-1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1__entry__2\">UINI_LOAD_ERROR</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tef1665702691693__table_d14816e1_d14817e1_d14818e1__entry__3\">No environment (<code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code> was\n                        not called), or you supplied a zero handle.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tef1665702691693__p_d119102e1_d119103e1_d119104e1\">We recommend that you use the mnemonic values rather than the numeric values. For example, you should test for UINI_SUCCESS rather than for 1. While this may make your code slightly harder to debug, it improves readability and portability.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tef1665702691693__topic_d84902e1_d84903e1_d84904e1_d84905e1_d84906e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d866720e192\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tef1665702691693__d5956e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucall</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tef1665702691693__topic_d84907e1_d84908e1_d84909e1_d84910e1_d84911e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d866720e204\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tef1665702691693__p_d119114e1_d119115e1_d119116e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">uedelete</code> shuts down the Uniface environment that was created by\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code>. By using the <var class=\"keyword varname\">how</var> parameter, you have\n            some control over how exactly this happens. (Note that this is only interesting for\n            character-mode applications, because a GUI application has no programmatic control over\n            keyboard and screen.) We recommend that you always use the value -1 for\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">how</var>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tef1665702691693__p_d119117e1_d119118e1_d119119e1\">Note that this function does not free the\n            environment handle. This is not important if <code class=\"ph codeph\">uedelete</code> is the last thing\n            you do in your program, but if you repeatedly call <code class=\"ph codeph\">uecreate</code> and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uedelete</code>, you should also free the environment handle after\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uedelete</code> by calling <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufreeh</code>. By not doing so, you\n            could cause a memory leak.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tef1665702691693__section_d5s_3ds_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d866720e243\">Example: uecreate, uedelete, ufreeh, uinstdel, uinstnew, uinstopr, and\n            uopract</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following simple call-in program shows how to activate the EXEC\n            operation of the service MYSVC. As usual, error checking has been omitted for the sake\n            of brevity.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104tef1665702691693_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"tef1665702691693__codeblock_oj5_mds_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n\nvoid main (void)\n{\nUHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */\nUHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */\nUHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */\nlong opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */\n\n/* Create the environment */\nuecreate(1, 0, 0, \"my.asn\", 0, 0, &amp;hEnv);\n/* Instantiate service MYSVC */\nuinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &amp;hIn, 0);\n\nuinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &amp;hOp); /* Instantiate the EXEC operation */\nuopract (hOp, &amp;opStat, 0); /* Activate the operation */\nuinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */\n\nufreeh (&amp;hOp); /* Free the operation */\nufreeh (&amp;hIn); /* Free the instance */\nuedelete(hEnv, -1); /* Shut down the environment */\nufreeh (&amp;hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */\nreturn 0; // on success\t\t\t\t\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532308\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532308\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uedelete Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Close down the Uniface environment that was created by uecreate . long uedelete (UHACT hEnv , int how ); Parameters hEnv The Uniface environment handle that was returned by uecreate . how A value specifying how you want to shut down the environment. Valid values are: 1—Suspend Uniface session, clear screen, and return control of keyboard and screen to the 3GL application. 0—Suspend Uniface session and return control of keyboard to the 3GL application. -1—Terminate the Uniface session completely. Return Values Table 1. Values returned by uedelete Value Error constant Meaning 1 UINI_SUCCESS Success -1 UINI_LOAD_ERROR No environment ( uecreate was not called), or you supplied a zero handle. We recommend that you use the mnemonic values rather than the numeric values. For example, you should test for UINI_SUCCESS rather than for 1. While this may make your code slightly harder to debug, it improves readability and portability. Use Library: ucall Description uedelete shuts down the Uniface environment that was created by uecreate . By using the how parameter, you have some control over how exactly this happens. (Note that this is only interesting for character-mode applications, because a GUI application has no programmatic control over keyboard and screen.) We recommend that you always use the value -1 for how . Note that this function does not free the environment handle. This is not important if uedelete is the last thing you do in your program, but if you repeatedly call uecreate and uedelete , you should also free the environment handle after uedelete by calling ufreeh . By not doing so, you could cause a memory leak. Example: uecreate, uedelete, ufreeh, uinstdel, uinstnew, uinstopr, and uopract The following simple call-in program shows how to activate the EXEC operation of the service MYSVC. As usual, error checking has been omitted for the sake of brevity. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> void main (void) { UHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */ UHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */ UHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */ long opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */ /* Create the environment */ uecreate(1, 0, 0, \"my.asn\", 0, 0, &hEnv); /* Instantiate service MYSVC */ uinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &hIn, 0); uinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &hOp); /* Instantiate the EXEC operation */ uopract (hOp, &opStat, 0); /* Activate the operation */ uinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */ ufreeh (&hOp); /* Free the operation */ ufreeh (&hIn); /* Free the instance */ uedelete(hEnv, -1); /* Shut down the environment */ ufreeh (&hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */ return 0; // on success } Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}